properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 11 at 1:57AM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...COMPLEX WINTER STORM WILL CONTINUE TO IMPACT THE REGION...

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation becoming freezing drizzle early this
morning, with another round of snow developing late this
afternoon. Additional snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches and
ice accumulations of a light glaze. Winds gusting as high as 35
mph.

* WHERE...Dane and Green Counties.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM CST SUNDAY... ...WINTER STORM WARNING IS CANCELLED
